“Strategies and Techniques with Health Law Experts,” Sandberg Phoenix Professional Development Series
Co-Presenter, “Illinois Work Product and Attorney-Client Rules and Practice Recommendations,” Sandberg Phoenix Professional Development Series
Co-Presenter, “The Last 100 Days Before Trial,” Sandberg Phoenix Professional Development Series



BIOGRAPHY
David Hoffman joined Sandberg Phoenix & von Gontard in 2003, and became a Shareholder in November 2012. He focuses his practice in the firm’s products liability and general litigation areas.
David has experience working on a variety of sports injury lawsuits, including issues related to supervision, faulty equipment, and the applicability of waivers. Prevention of sports-related injuries and lawsuits is of keen interest to him as well. As such, he lectures on risk management issues to a variety of local businesses and recreational professionals.
Trucking and transportation are also areas of specialty for David. He is experienced in litigating trucking cases in both Missouri and Illinois, and obtained a defense verdict in a wrongful death case involving a truck in Pettis County, Missouri in 2011.
David is also no stranger to appellate work. He has successfully argued appeals in the Courts of Appeal for the Eastern and Southern Districts of Missouri. His first published appeal is Hooe v. Saint Francis Medical Center, et al, 284 S.W.3d. 738 (Mo.Ct.App.2009).
In 2009, David was named as a Rising Star by the Missouri & Kansas Super Lawyers publication. David was also named in 2009 by Missouri Lawyers Weekly as one of Missouri’s “Up and Coming Lawyers.” For his outstanding work in Product Liability Litigation Defense, David was selected by his peers as a Best Lawyer for inclusion in Best Lawyers in America in 2016 and 2017.











 
